The goal of a present course is to study the basic functions of human body - from the molecular level to the level of whole organism. A special attention is paid to the teaching of physiological role of sensory and central nervous system.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Physiology belongs to the fundamental sciences in medicine. Knowing of physiology is essential to medical doctor in order to understand the normal functioning of human body. Without this knowledge it is impossible to understand the process of saving and restoring of health.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completion of the course, the student should be able to: Define the fundamental physiological terms. Explain the mechanisms for regulation of the different body functions. Explain how regulatory mechanisms can recover equilibrium and function when the homeostasis is disturbed in a physiological system. Understand the physiological background of clinical problems. Understand and be able to use simple instruments to measure physiological parameters.
